description: A pair of yellow vented bulbul adults perching on a bamboo branch. It has a prominent white supercilium contrasting its dark crown. Its vent is yellow. It also has a black eye-stripe and a black bill. It has brown remiges and rectrices, with a lighter coloured belly. Indeterminate sex, they generally do not show sexual dimorphism, although females can be smaller in size.
